articles.headline: Watkins slips backdoor for alley-oop

articles.description: Rasheem Dunn scored 24 and hit a go-ahead layup late and St. Francis (Brooklyn) sank 5 of 6 free throws in the final 33 seconds to hold off LIU Brooklyn 84-79 on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Dunn rallies St Francis to 84-79 win over LIU Brooklyn

articles.description: Jason Dunne scored 19 points with four 3-pointers and nine rebounds, J.R. Lynch scored 13 points and made four free throws in the final 16 seconds, and Hartford beat Maine 67-63 on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Lynch's free throws help Hartford down Maine 67-63

articles.description: James Scott and Nick Masterson each scored 27 points, Anthony Wilson calmly sank two free throws on his first trip to the line with 1.1 seconds on the clock and Kennesaw State defeated Florida Gulf Coast 97-93 Thursday night, ending the Eagles'...
articles.headline: Kennesaw State beats FGCU 97-93, ending 13-game win streak

articles.description: Shaquille Morris had 23 points and 13 rebounds, including a tie-breaking putback in the final two minutes, to help No. 19 Wichita State defeat Temple 93-86 on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Morris leads No. 19 Wichita State past Temple 93-86

images.caption: Zach Brown misses the triple, but Shaquille Morris is there to clean up for the lay-in and the foul.
images.name: Morris' and-1 bucket gives the Shockers the lead

articles.description: Corey Davis Jr. and Devin Davis each scored 16 points, and Houston beat No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62 on Thursday night to snap the nation's longest winning streak at 16 games.
articles.headline: Houston ends No. 5 Cincinnati's 16-game win streak, 67-62

images.caption: The student section celebrates Houston's first win over an AP top-5 team since 1996.
images.name: Houston' student section storms the court after W

videos.description: Jordan Murphy rejects a Miami player at the rim and Nate Mason drains a 3-pointer at the other end to get the Minnesota crowd into the game.
videos.headline: Gophers' block sets up 3-pointer to awaken crowd

videos.description: Hurricanes guard Chris Lykes sneaks in to get a steal and manages to keep his balance along the sideline before scoring an easy transition layup.
videos.headline: Miami's Lykes steals, tiptoes sideline, and scores

videos.description: Amir Coffey drives the lane, absorbs contact and adjusts mid-air to get the hoop and the harm.
videos.headline: Coffey converts acrobatic layup for Gophers and-1

videos.description: Gophers guard Amir Coffey misses a layup and falls to the floor, but the ball bounces back to him and he makes the shot from his backside.
videos.headline: Minnesota player makes shot from the ground

videos.description: Hurricanes forward Dewan Huell rises up and slams home a powerful dunk over two Minnesota defenders.
videos.headline: Miami's Huell puts two defenders on a poster

videos.description: The Hurricanes get a steal, and on the fast break Ja'Quan Newton throws a lob to Bruce Brown Jr. who slams it home.
videos.headline: Brown rises to throw down alley-oop for Miami

videos.description: Hurricanes freshman guard Lonnie Walker IV snares a defensive rebound and takes it all the way to the other end to convert an and-1 layup.
videos.headline: Miami's Walker goes coast-to-coast for and-1

videos.description: Nate Mason dishes to Reggie Lynch who flushes down a two-handed dunk despite being fouled.
videos.headline: Gophers' Lynch slams home powerful dunk through contact

videos.description: Dewan Huell extends Miami's late lead, rising high and slamming over a Minnesota defender to convert the and-1 dunk.
videos.headline: Miami's Huell skies for powerful flush

videos.description: Fran Fraschilla and Clay Matvick break down the Hurricanes' 86-81 against the Gophers, citing Dewan Huell's big night and Miami's "outstanding guard play" as the keys to the victory.
videos.headline: Miami impresses in road win against Minnesota
